{"pageProps":{"article":{"title":"Traditional Gingerbread Madness","category":"On the Menu","subcategory":"Recipes","publish_date":"2016-12-24T08:00:00.000Z","full_thumbnail":"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/IMG_1105.jpg?resize=355%2C230&ssl=1","mobile_thumbnail":"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/IMG_1105.jpg?resize=980%2C647&ssl=1","description":"\"Every year in early December my family gathers from all across California, not to spread Christmas cheer, but to engage in a fierce competition\"","content":"<div class=\"single-post-content\">\n            <div id=\"attachment_74629\" style=\"width: 1034px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-74629\" data-attachment-id=\"74629\" data-permalink=\"https://dailynexus.com/2016-12-24/traditional-gingerbread-madness/img_1105/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/IMG_1105.jpg?fit=3264%2C2448&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"3264,2448\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta='{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"0\"}' data-image-title=\"img_1105\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/IMG_1105.jpg?fit=250%2C188&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/IMG_1105.jpg?fit=888%2C666&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"size-large wp-image-74629\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/IMG_1105-1024x768.jpg?resize=888%2C666\" alt=\"Marisa Ratchford / Daily Nexus\" width=\"888\" height=\"666\" srcset=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/IMG_1105.jpg?resize=1024%2C768&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/IMG_1105.jpg?resize=250%2C188&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/IMG_1105.jpg?resize=768%2C576&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/IMG_1105.jpg?w=1776 1776w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/IMG_1105.jpg?w=2664 2664w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><p id=\"caption-attachment-74629\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Marisa Ratchford / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>\n<p>Every year in early December my family gathers from all across California, not to spread Christmas cheer, but to engage in a fierce competition. My huge Italian family is stuffed inside my grandmother’s house, which is filled with the scent of gingerbread and peppermint. My cousins fight over the remote while my uncles stammer through jokes between sips of beer. In the kitchen, aunts and the older cousins eagerly wait for the first batch of my grandmother’s gingerbread to finally finish cooking.</p>\n<p>We all gather like this for our annual gingerbread house competition, a contest that originally began as a way to spend more time together during the winter months. It all started years ago as a simple suggestion that the family spend more time together while everyone is home for the holidays. After all, our Christmas celebration often unravels into a hectic mess of Grab Bag games and scrambling to clean up wrapping paper. It’s hard to spend time with people when you’re trying to hand out presents to your 10 cousins.</p>\n<p>This idea to spend more time together soon evolved into a competition of creativity between the kids of the family. Originally, we all began with the same pre-assembled pieces that come in an average gingerbread making kit. But every year we added more creative elements and plenty of trash talk to take down the competition. As my cousins and I got older we became more crafty when assembling our gingerbread dream-homes. In recent years, we’ve started ignoring the pre-assembled kits and 